OL,3,CPaedophile who fled to 'paradise' for
OL,4,C27 years finally stands trial
OL,6,FBurrows, originally from Birmingham,
OL,7,Fdenies four counts of buggery, two
OL,8,Fcounts of indecency with a child, two
OL,9,Fcounts of attempted buggery and 47
OL,10,Findecent assaults against 10
OL,11,Fcomplainants aged between nine and 15,
OL,12,Ffrom the mid-1960s to the mid-1990s.
OL,14,FAs complainants of sexual offences,
OL,15,Fnone of the victims can be identified.
OL,17,FMark Connor, opening the case for the
OL,18,Fprosecution, told the jury of eight
OL,19,Fwomen and four men that, over many
OL,20,Fyears, Burrows systematically abused
OL,21,Fboys with whom he came into contact.
