OL,3,CPaedophile who fled to 'paradise' for
OL,4,C27 years finally stands trial
OL,6,FMr Connor said: "He obtained positions
OL,7,Fof trust and responsibility which he
OL,8,Fbreached to satisfy himself sexually
OL,9,Fwith the youngsters."
OL,11,FBurrows had worked as a housemaster at
OL,12,Fa school in Cheshire in the 1960s,
OL,13,Fwhere he allegedly preyed on
OL,14,Fvulnerable youngsters.
OL,16,FHe was also involved in the Scouts as
OL,17,Fa leader, and was involved in amateur
OL,18,Fradio clubs.
