OL,3,CPaedophile who fled to 'paradise' for
OL,4,C27 years finally stands trial
OL,6,FThe jury was told Burrows admits
OL,7,Findecent assault and sexual touching
OL,8,Fof some of the boys in his care.
OL,10,FBut he denies abusing other youngsters
OL,11,Fand any penetrative sexual activity,
OL,12,Fdrawing a distinction between that and
OL,13,Fsexual touching, which he appears to
OL,14,Fsuggest is justified because in his
OL,15,Fmind he did no harm, the jury was told.
OL,17,FHe claims the complainants in this
OL,18,Ftrial are either mistaken about the
OL,19,Fidentity of the perpetrator or are
OL,20,Flying.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
